'''Diego Aduarte''' [[Dominican Order|OP]] (1570–1636; born in [[Zaragoza]]) was a Spanish [[Dominican Order|Dominican friar]] and [[historian]]. He was a [[missionary]] to the Philippine Islands and in 1632 was made Prior of [[Manila]], where he died in 1637.

Aduarte works include an account of the difficulties and problems faced by Spanish missionaries introducing Christianity into [[Cambodia]].

