'''Ortwin Gamber''' (born 21 March 1925) is an Austrian art historian and director of the weapons collection at the [[Kunsthistorisches Museum]] from 1976 to 1986. He had previously volunteered and following his 1950 graduation, worked at the museum since 1945. He is also a noted weapon collector, and has written several books and articles on the subject.

==Career==
[[File:Italian - Sallet - Walters 51580.jpg|thumb|alt=Colour photograph of a suit of armour|Italian suit of armour with [[sallet]], {{circa}} 1450]]
Ortwin Gamber was born on 21 March 1925 in [[Enns (town)|Enns]], [[Upper Austria]].{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|p=359}} Studying under [[Karl Maria Swoboda]] ([[:de:Karl Maria Swoboda|de]]), he obtained his [[Ph.D.]] from the [[University of Vienna]] in 1950, with the thesis ''Der Plattenharnisch im 15. Jahrhundert'' ("The [[plate armor]] in the 15th century").{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|pp=359–360}} He also studied from 1948 to 1950 at the [[Institut für Österreichische Geschichtsforschung]] ([[:de:Institut für Österreichische Geschichtsforschung|de]]), passing the [[Staatsexamen]] with the thesis ''Die Innsbrucker Plattnerei von 1450 bis zum Tode Kaiser Maximilians I'' ("The Innsbruck Armoury from 1450 Until the Death of Emperor Maximilian I"); during his studies, from 1945 until 1950, he also volunteered at the weapons collection of the [[Kunsthistorisches Museum]] in [[Vienna]].{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|p=359}} Following his graduation, in 1950 Gamber was hired for a staff position at the Kunsthistorisches Museum.{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|p=359}} He was variously promoted over the succeeding quarter-century, and from 1976 until 1986 served as the director of the weapons collection there.{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|p=359}}

In 1962, Gamber was awarded the [[Theodor Körner Prize]].{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|p=359}} The same year he was made an honorary member of the [[Arms and Armour Society]] ([[:de:Arms and Armour Society|de]]).{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|p=359}}

==Publications==
Gamber has written dozens of articles on the subject of arms and armour.{{sfn|Broucek|Peball|2000|pp=359–362}} The list below is incomplete; a more complete list appears in {{harvnb|Broucek|Peball|2000}}.
* {{cite journal | ref = harv | last = Gamber | first = Ortwin | translator-last = Eaves | translator-first = Ian | date = December 1982 | title = Some Notes on the Sutton Hoo Military Equipment | journal = The Journal of the Arms & Armour Society | location = London | series = | volume = X | issue = 6 | pages = 208–216 | issn = 0004-2439 }}

