'''Phillip Gowan''' (October 17, 1952 &ndash; May 1, 2018), was an [[United States of America|American]] [[RMS Titanic]] historian.
Born in [[Corsicana, Texas]] on October 17, 1952 from Theodore Phillip "Ted" Gowan and Julia Thedia "Judy" Morris Gowan, he graduated from [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and business at [[Howard Payne University]]. He was really interested in genealogy and travelling since a child which he later demonstrated throughout his research on the Titanic.<ref>[http://obituaries.corsicanadailysun.com/obituary/phil-gowan-1058661956 Phil's Story]</ref> The parents-in-law of his mother perished on the disaster<ref>[http://www.umc.org/who-we-are/reflections-on-the-titanic-historian-phil-gowan Reflections on the Titanic: Historian Phil Gowan]</ref>.
His research field focused more on passengers and crew, and the [[Sinking of RMS Titanic|sinking]] itself, getting exclusive photographs and stories that he made public and interviewing several survivors, like [[Milvina Dean]] and the families of those who died.<ref>[http://events.dfw.cbslocal.com/arlington/events/phil-gowan-history-titanic-/E0-001-045405052-8 Phil Gowan - The History of the Titanic]</ref> He's also known for his accurate calculation of the number of passengers on board, calculation that bears the name ''Gowan Numbers'': 1,496 people died and 712 survived.<ref>[http://titanicnewschannel.com/blog/tag/phil-gowan/ RECENT TITANIC NEWS: TITANIC SURVIVOR ACCUSED OF COWARDICE CLEARED;DEATH OF TITANIC EXPERT]</ref> He participated in several international congresses about the Titanic as a guest by [[Titanic Historical Society]], was interviewed by [[National Geographic]]<ref>[https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Titanic-survivor-status-in-question-3618124.php Titanic survivor status in question]</ref> <ref>[http://www.nationalgeographic.com.au/history/15-facts-about-the-titanic.aspx 15 FACTS ABOUT THE TITANIC]</ref> and television networks of several countries of the world; and published articles in newspapers. Although having serious illnesses during his life, he lost the battle against cancer on May 1, 2018 at the age of 65, being recognized by many as a renowned Titanic historian.
